<h2 id="section-top">Therapy services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=29674">Derbyshire Community Health Services NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent2e185a3ca6274e92b4bba58cb39a1e7e">
</div>
<p><br/><strong>Who we are</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>We deliver community therapy services in partnership with Derbyshire Adult Social Services and other statutory and voluntary agencies. </p>
<p>Our community therapy services are provided in the home and other community settings for vulnerable, elderly or frail people and their carers.<br/><br/><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>What we do</strong></p>
<p>We provide physiotherapy and Occupational Therapy assessment, treatment and advice for individuals in their own home, working jointly with patients and their carers to establish goals and priorities.</p>
<p>The service is available to individuals who are unable to access an outpatient department or where the home environment needs to be considered as part of the assessment and treatment process.<br/><br/><strong>Service locations </strong></p>
<p>Community Therapy Services are provided across Derbyshire in patients homes and community residential settings with bases at the following locations;</p>
<p>Erewash – base at Ilkeston Community Hospital and Long Eaton Health Centre<br/>Amber Valley – base at Babington Hospital<br/>North East Derbyshire – base at Clay Cross Hospital <br/>Bolsover – base at Bolsover Hospital<br/>Chesterfield - base at Walton Hospital<br/>High Peak and Dales – base at Cavendish Hospital and Newholme Hospital<br/>Derbyshire Dales – base at Whitworth Hospital  <br/>South Derbyshire  - base at St Oswalds Hospital and Repton Health Centre</p>
<p><br/><strong>Opening times</strong></p>
<p>The Community Therapy Service is available <strong>8.30am – 5pm Monday to Friday. </strong><br/><br/><br/><strong>Contact </strong></p>
<p>For more information about the service, please contact your local community manager;</p>
<p><br/>Erewash area<br/>Esther Jennison-Boyle, Tel: </p>
